            <div id="feature-section">
                <h1 class="feature-section-title"> The top places to visit in <i>Lakshwadeep</i></h1>
                <div class="feature-content">
                    <div class="cols-3">
                        <img src="bangaramIsland.jpg"> 
                        <h3> Bangaram Island </h3>
                        <p> Bangaram Island is known for its pristine beaches, the vibrant coral reefs, many different fishes and few of the adventure sports. </p>
                    </div>    
                    <div class="cols-3">   
                        <img src="kadmatIsland.jpg"> 
                        <h3> Kadmat Island </h3>
                        <p> Kadmat Island, also known as Cardamom Island, is a coral island belonging to the Amindivi subgroup of islands of the Lakshadweep archipelago in India.</p>  
                    </div>    
                    <div class="cols-3">   
                        <img src="kalpeniIsland.jpg"> 
                        <h3> Kalpeni Island </h3>
                        <p> Kalpeni is most famous for Tip Beach, a white sandy beach with a shallow emerald colored lagoon and clean pristine water ideal for diving, snorkeling, even a casual afternoon dip.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="cols-3">  
                        <img src="minicoyIsland.jpg"> 
                        <h3> Minicoy Island </h3>
                        <p>  It is the second largest and southern most island in Lakshadweep, crescent shaped and has one of the largest lagoons. </p>
                    </div>    
                </div>
            </div>
